    <briefdescription>
<para>GetFolderItems response. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The items[] array contains a sequence of items, where each item starts with a <ref refid="structbt__avrcp__item__hdr" kindref="compound">bt_avrcp_item_hdr</ref> structure. Based on the item_type field in the header, the application should parse the item using the corresponding structure:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>item_type = BT_AVRCP_ITEM_TYPE_MEDIA_PLAYER (0x01): Parse as <ref refid="structbt__avrcp__media__player__item" kindref="compound">bt_avrcp_media_player_item</ref></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>item_type = BT_AVRCP_ITEM_TYPE_FOLDER (0x02): Parse as <ref refid="structbt__avrcp__folder__item" kindref="compound">bt_avrcp_folder_item</ref></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>item_type = BT_AVRCP_ITEM_TYPE_MEDIA_ELEMENT (0x03): Parse as <ref refid="structbt__avrcp__media__element__item" kindref="compound">bt_avrcp_media_element_item</ref></para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>All multi-octet fields are in big-endian format and need conversion using <ref refid="sys_2byteorder_8h_1a840037a5fd3d36817dc92a44469df704" kindref="member">sys_be16_to_cpu()</ref>, <ref refid="sys_2byteorder_8h_1aee4cefae7f089197e77c487faafda269" kindref="member">sys_be32_to_cpu()</ref> etc. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
